    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-06-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Alan Chester, Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    Mr. Day’s note, No. 713, of the 28th instant, stating that the proposal of Her
                    Majesty’s Government for a renewal of the arrangement of 1894 relative to the
                    sealing regulations in Bering Sea is not acceptable to your Government.</p>
                <p>I shall not fail to bring the contents of this note to the knowledge of Her
                    Majesty’s principal secretary of state for foreign affairs.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reginald Tower.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
